<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AFC G-07917 - Aftertreatment Calibration and Enhanced Diagnosis</stitle>
    <afc id="afc07917">
        <afcnum>G-07917</afcnum>
        <afcdate>February, 2008</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>Engine</subjectfile>
        <subject>Aftertreatment Calibration and Enhanced Diagnosis</subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>MaxxForce DT
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>03/01/2007</startdate>
                        <enddate>11/27/2007</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </engfam>
                <engfam>MaxxForce 9
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>03/01/2007</startdate>
                        <enddate>11/27/2007</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </engfam>
                <engfam>MaxxForce 10
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>03/01/2007</startdate>
                        <enddate>11/27/2007</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This AFC applies to all trucks and or buses that are equipped with MaxxForce DT, 9 and 10
                    engines.
                </para>
                <para>Some engines in the date range above have experienced unnecessary warning lights, unsuccessful DPF
                    regeneration and/or the need for frequent regens. This software upgrade addresses these issues and
                    provides additional improvements.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="14">
            <title>Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>First check to see if the ECM has latest software that applies to the engine you are working on.
            </para>
            <para>DLC Auto Upgrade is a software program that enables users to upgrade the calibration on all engine
                controllers produced after three box systems. This software allows users to upgrade engine calibrations
                without having to use the NETS system and required internet connections. DLC Auto Upgrade allows a
                technician to program the latest engine calibration in up to 75 trucks within a 72 hour period without
                connecting to the Internet.
            </para>
            <para>IF YOU HAVEN'T ALREADY DOWNLOADED DLC AUTO UPGRADE, FOLLOW THESE INSTRUCTIONS</para>
            <para>DLC Auto Upgrade is available at the Download Center. Look for the program labeled
                <emph type="bold">AutoUpgradeEngine</emph>.
                <exhotlnk
                        document="https://evalue.internationaldelivers.com/service/FntUsr/FAQ2/vehicle%20programming/Download%20Center.pdf"
                        bookname="EXTERNAL">Click here for instructions about how to use the Download Center.</exhotlnk>
                . After installing the program. use the following instructions as a users guide.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Launch DLC Auto Upgrade from Engine Diags on the EZ-Tech GUI (Figure 1).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073801" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073801.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Log in to the DLC Auto Upgrade program with your username and password (Figure 2).
                    (Requires DLB certified username permission level.)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073802" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073802.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Select the cable that you will be using (Figure 3).</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>DLC Auto Upgrade will only program in high speed mode when the IC4USB cable is used.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f073803" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073803.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the communication cable to the vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the International Engine Reprogramming Harness with the switch in the
                    <emph type="bold">OFF</emph>
                    position. SFN 07-29 describes how to use and connect the harness.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press the Start button (Figure 4).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073804" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073804.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the International Engine Reprogramming Harness ON when the DLC Auto Upgrade program
                    prompts for the Ignition Key ON (Figure 5).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073805" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073805.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the harness OFF when the program prompts for the Ignition Key OFF (Figure 6).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073806" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073806.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the harness ON when the program prompts for the Ignition Key ON (Figure 7).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073807" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073807.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the calibration doesn't need upgraded, the program will say "No upgrade available" (Figure
                        8).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f073808" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073808.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the harness OFF when the program prompts for the Ignition Key OFF (Figure 9).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073809" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073809.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the harness ON when the program prompts for the Ignition Key ON (Figure 10).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073810" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073810.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the harness OFF when the program prompts for the Ignition Key OFF (Figure 11).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073811" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073811.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The update is complete (Figure 12).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f073812" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073812.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the harness and reinsert the ECM power fuse that you were instructed to
                    remove when you went through the instructions in SFN-07-29.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the vehicle ignition key on.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the program is complete by checking Service Assistant (Master Diagnostics) for
                    any active DTCs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If there is an error during programming you will have to fix the problem (i.e.; battery
                        voltage, cable is accidentally disconnected, laptop's battery is low and the laptop turns off,
                        etc.) select the VIN.exe file in the recover menu.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f073813" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073813.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Example of Error</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f073814" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g073814.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="192px"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Select the VIN.exe and press OK</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Contact Vehicle Programming at 1-800-336-4500 option 2 then option 3 for help and assistance.</para>
        </svcproc>
